## Hook Configuration

### Hook Type
- [ ] **PreToolUse**: Execute before tool calls for validation/security
- [ ] **PostToolUse**: Execute after tool calls for logging/cleanup
- [ ] **Notification**: Handle system notifications and alerts
- [ ] **Stop**: Execute when Claude Code session stops
- [ ] **SubagentStop**: Execute when sub-agent execution completes

### Purpose
[Detailed description of what this hook accomplishes and why it's needed]

### Execution Context
- **Trigger Event**: [Specific event that activates this hook]
- **Context Available**: [What information is passed to the hook]
- **Expected Actions**: [What the hook should do with the context]

## Hook Implementation Template

```javascript
#!/usr/bin/env node

/**
 * [Hook Name] Hook
 * [Detailed description of hook purpose and functionality]
 */

const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');

class [HookClassName]Hook {
  constructor(options = {}) {
    this.frameworkPath = options.frameworkPath || process.cwd();
    this.hookType = '[hook-type]';
    this.enableLogging = options.enableLogging !== false;
    this.logLevel = options.logLevel || 'info';

    // Hook-specific configuration
    this.[configOption1] = options.[configOption1] || [defaultValue];
    this.[configOption2] = options.[configOption2] || [defaultValue];
  }

  /**
   * Main hook execution method
   * @param {Object} context - Hook execution context
   */
  async execute(context = {}) {
    try {
      console.log(`ğŸ”— Executing [Hook Name] hook...`);

      // Pre-execution validation
      await this.validateContext(context);

      // Main hook logic
      const result = await this.performHookActions(context);

      // Post-execution cleanup
      await this.cleanup(result, context);

      return result;

    } catch (error) {
      await this.handleError(error, context);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  /**
   * Validate hook execution context
   */
  async validateContext(context) {
    // Validate required context properties
    // Throw error if context is invalid
  }

  /**
   * Perform main hook actions - override in specific implementations
   */
  async performHookActions(context) {
    // Implement hook-specific logic here
    throw new Error('performHookActions must be implemented by specific hook');
  }

  /**
   * Cleanup after hook execution
   */
  async cleanup(result, context) {
    // Cleanup logic if needed
  }

  /**
   * Error handling for hook execution
   */
  async handleError(error, context) {
    this.log('error', `Hook execution failed: ${error.message}`, {
      hookType: this.hookType,
      context: context,
      error: error.stack
    });
  }

  /**
   * Logging utility
   */
  log(level, message, data = {}) {
    if (!this.enableLogging) return;

    const logEntry = {
      timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
      level,
      hook: this.hookType,
      message,
      ...data
    };

    console.log(`[${level.toUpperCase()}] ${this.hookType}: ${message}`);

    // Optional: Write to log file
    if (this.logFile) {
      this.appendToLogFile(logEntry);
    }
  }

  /**
   * Append log entry to file
   */
  appendToLogFile(logEntry) {
    try {
      const logLine = JSON.stringify(logEntry) + '\n';
      fs.appendFileSync(this.logFile, logLine);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Failed to write to log file:', error.message);
    }
  }
}

module.exports = [HookClassName]Hook;
